definition: Taiwan pr. used in 夾生|夹生[jia1 sheng1] and 夾竹桃|夹竹桃[jia1 zhu2 tao2]
to press from either side/to place in between/to sandwich/to carry sth under armpit/wedged between/between/to intersperse/to mix/to mingle/clip/folder/Taiwan pr. [jia2]

sentences.english: I took out my wallet and nervously fumbled for the pictures of my family.
sentences.chinese: 我拿出了皮夹，慌手慌脚地翻出了我的全家福照片。

sentences.english: Can use in the billfold , woof, paperboard & book.
sentences.chinese: 可用于皮夹，布料，厚纸，书类。

sentences.english: I’m looking for a leather jacket for my son.
sentences.chinese: 我想给我的儿子买一件皮夹克。

sentences.english: I took out my walled and nervously fumbled for the pictures of my family.
sentences.chinese: 说着，我摸出皮夹，哆哆嗦嗦地掏出了家人的照片。

sentences.english: Some dig-ital money providers refer to the account as an electronic wallet.
sentences.chinese: 一些数位钱供给者提及帐户如一个电子的皮夹。

sentences.english: He stood up and felt for his wallet in his pocket.
sentences.chinese: 他站起身，然后摸了摸裤兜里的皮夹子。

sentences.english: He was wearing green army pants, and a turtleneck, and a leather jacket.
sentences.chinese: 他穿了一条军绿色的裤子，高领毛衣，皮夹克。

sentences.english: My leather jacket the one smells like actual cattle?
sentences.chinese: 就是那件闻起来像头牛的皮夹克？

sentences.english: Harley - Davidson begins selling what will become the classic black leather motorcycle jacket .
sentences.chinese: 哈雷戴维森开始销售经典的黑色摩托皮夹克。

sentences.english: After she paid the bill, she placed the receipt in her wallet.
sentences.chinese: 她付了款之后把收据放进皮夹子里。

sentences.english: He was being accused of persuading a friend to take the wallet back.
sentences.chinese: 他正受到指责，说他转托一位朋友送回这皮夹子。

sentences.english: And the Star-Child took the piece of yellow gold, and put it in his wallet, and hurried to the city.
sentences.chinese: 星孩捞起了黄金，把它放在皮夹里，匆匆往城里赶去。

sentences.english: Neville had been sobbing into Hagrid's jacket for the last five minutes.
sentences.chinese: 罗恩说，尼维尔激动得扑在他的皮夹上哭了五分钟。
